metadata.name: Intermeso 12:13
metadata.description:
intermeso

or


in·ter·mez·zo  
/ˌin(t)ərˈmetsō/  
 Learn to pronounce  
noun  
noun: intermezzo; plural noun: intermezzi; plural noun: intermezzos  
a short connecting instrumental movement in an opera or other musical work.  
a short piece of music for a solo instrument.  
a light dramatic, musical, or other performance inserted between the acts of a play.

12:13, after lunch
